article.headline: Arkansas St. 84, Florida Atlantic 77
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Arkansas State's Adrian Banks went 6-for-11 from 3-point range Wednesday night, finishing with 22 points in an 84-77 victory over Sun Belt Conference rival Florida Atlantic. Banks was also generous to his teammates, dishing out six assists. Arkansas State (12-11, 7-4 SBC) enjoyed an evening of accuracy from the field overall, hitting 11-of-22 long-distance shots and making 54 percent of its field goal attempts. Isaac Wells contributed 14 points for ASU and got a double-double with 10 rebounds, while Ryan Wedel also scored 14, Jim Jones added 13 and Shawn Morgan scored 11. DeAndre Rice of Florida Atlantic (10-12, 6-6) topped all scorers with 32 points. Teammate Carlos Monroe also doubled up on the night, with 22 points and 12 rebounds, and Paul Graham added 10 points.
